Description: Round, well-smoothed bone disc, thicker in the middle, getting thinner to the edges. Four parallel lines in central part, running over complete front side, incised and inlayed with blue paste. Distance between lines between 1.5 and 2mm. Maybe some sort of inlay.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), D14.8, level 3, bin near mastaba
Bibliographic references: Spencer 1997 / Amara West I, The Architectural Report (p. 138)
